# Logs
logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
lerna-debug.log*

# Local build/test scratch logs (build.err, preview.out, sitegen.err, etc.)
*.err
*.out

node_modules
dist
dist-ssr
*.local

# Per-post + per-product Open Graph cards — regenerated deterministically at
# prebuild via scripts/generate-og-images.mjs, and Vercel runs prebuild on
# every deploy. Keeping them out of git avoids a ~3 MB diff every time a
# title changes (one file per slug). The fallback og-image.png is still
# committed. .og-blog-cache.json is the legacy cache filename kept here
# during the rename window.
public/og-blog-*.png
public/og-product-*.png
public/.og-blog-cache.json
public/.og-card-cache.json

# Environment — NEVER commit secrets
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Editor directories and files
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
.idea
.DS_Store
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.sw?
.vercel
.env*.local

# Claude Code local agent scratch
.claude/

# OneDrive / Google Drive restore duplicates — patterns like ".env(1).vault",
# "dist(2)/", ".claude(1)/" that cloud-sync tools create when they restore
# previously-deleted files. They always match "something (N)" or "something(N)".
*\ \(?\)*
*\(?\)*
*\ \(??\)*
*\(??\)*

# Private strategy / TODO / setup docs — live alongside the repo in
# SimpleITSRQ/private-notes/, never in git. If these patterns match a
# file in the working tree, they will be ignored on every commit.
USER-TODO.md
PASSIVE-INCOME-ROADMAP.md
CLOUDFLARE-ZERO-TRUST-SETUP.md
WEBAUTHN-IMPLEMENTATION-PLAN.md
SITE-INVENTORY.md
*-PLAN.md
*-ROADMAP.md
*-SETUP.md
*-TODO.md
